Pushing: Local PC to GitHub
1 Create a repository on GitHub to hold your project.
2 Initialize Git in your local project folder using git init.
3 Stage files using git add . to prepare them for uploading.
4 Commit changes locally with git commit -m "Your message".
5 Link repositories using git remote add origin YOUR_URL.
6 Push code to GitHub using the git push -u origin main command.



Pulling: GitHub to Local PC
1 Download repositories the first time by using git clone YOUR_URL.
2 Fetch updates that other people made using the git fetch command.
3 Merge updates into your local code automatically using git pull.
4 Stay updated by pulling fresh changes every day before you